===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|羋|山|t1=sheep bleat|t2=mountain}}: rebus of {{zh-l|*羋}} for {{zh-l|*岳}}, with {{zh-l|*山}} added as semantic component.<ref>陈年福：《实用甲骨文字典》，四川辞书出版社2019年版，P.409</ref>

===Etymology 1===
Unclear. Compare Proto-{{w|Bahnaric languages#North Bahnaric|North Bahnaric}} *''ŋŏk'' ("mountain") (> {{cog|hal|ngŏk}} and {{cog|sed|ŋɔ}}). Note also {{cog|qfa-lic-pro|*hŋwʔo³||mountain}} and perhaps also {{cog|my|ငေါ}}, {{m|my|tr=ŋok-ŋak|t=project, stick up or out}}, {{m|my|tr=ŋroŋʼ|t=any sharp thing sticking out; sharp stump or thorn}}, and {{cog|bo|རྔོག|t=hump}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

STEDT instead derives it from provisional {{inh|zh|sit-pro||*kak|expensive, at its peak}} and considers it cognate to {{och-l|極|tr=*N‑kək; ''N‑k(r)ək''|ridge of house; the highest point; extreme limit, utmost}}, {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*kak||expensive, intense, at its peak}} (> {{cog|lis|tr=phy²¹ '''kha³⁵'''|t=expensive}}), {{cog|ers|phɛ⁵⁵ '''khuɑ⁵⁵'''||expensive}}, and {{cog|adl|`kog dɨr|'''`kog''' dɨr |t=peak}}.

